The paper deals with information theory and mathematical statistics, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as it directly relates to the topic of the paper. cs.ITP (Information Theory and Probability) is also a likely category as the paper deals with entropy and divergence measures, which are closely related to probability theory. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper involves mathematical proofs and characterizations. cs.MS (Mathematical Statistics) is another possible category as the paper deals with statistical measures. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a less likely category as the paper does not involve any machine learning algorithms or applications, but it does deal with information measures that are relevant to machine learning.
